{"id":"sherebiah","term":"Sherebiah","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Flame of the Lord, a priest whose name is prominent in connection with the work carried on by Ezra and Nehemiah at Jerusalem (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 8:17\">Ezra 8:17</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 8:18\">18</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:24\">24-30</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 8:7\">Neh. 8:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 9:4\">9:4</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 9:5\">5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 10:12\">10:12</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Ezra 8:17","Ezra 8:18","Genesis 1:24","Nehemiah 8:7","Nehemiah 9:4","Nehemiah 9:5","Nehemiah 10:12"]}